One very important thing that was not mentioned is that CO2 in a swimming pool is EXTREMELY dangerous. Since CO2 is heavier than air it will settle on the surface of the water, coincidentally where your head is, and can cause suffocation (several people died that way from putting dry ice in a pool for a 'cool fog effect').
On a brighter note seeing how much propulsion you got guys got from 850-ish psi it would be interesting to see an even higher pressure tanks. Nitrogen is 2200 psi, scuba tanks can go up to 3500. I believe nitrogen is what's used by space walking astronauts for maneuvering. There are small jets in their suits that help them orient themselves when they are not holding on to something.
